4.content:
Hello Kate!

Welcome to Boston Hospital!
I am Bob, the managing director of the hospital.
4.name: Dialogue State

17.content: Congratulations on your new job as a Supply Chain Director.
17.name: Dialogue State

32.content:
There are 2 types of patients:

Urgent patients and Non-urgent patients.
32.name: Dialogue State

293.content: Now let me show you your office.
293.name: Dialogue State

23137.content:
You have two main tasks:

First, to administer {drugName} to meet current demand.
23137.name: Dialogue State

23139.content: Just keep in mind that there are high costs for maintaining too much inventory.
23139.name: Dialogue State

23142.content: Second, to ensure sufficient {drugName} inventory to treat future unexpected demands.
23142.name: Dialogue State

24121.content: You can review your goal by clicking on this button.
24121.name: Dialogue State

24153.action_text: Goal: Minimize Cost! (Total cost: ${costTotal}) 1) Administer {drugName} to meet current demand. 2) Ensure sufficient {drugName} inventory to treat future unexpected demands.

24281.content: This button shows how many patients you have treated with {drugName} and how many with the replacement drugs.
24281.name: Dialogue State

24294.content: You can check the inventory costs by clicking on this button.
24294.name: Dialogue State

24315.action_text: Patients treated with replacement drugs: Urgent patients {cumUntreatedU} (${cumRepCostU}) Non-urgent patients {cumUntreatedNU} (${cumRepCostNU}) Total patients {cumLost} (${cumRepCostTotal})

26264.content: Your main goal is to minimize the overall cost to the hospital.
26264.name: Dialogue State

26265.content: The overall cost consists of the inventory cost and the cost of treating patients with replacement drugs in case we're out of {drugName}.
26265.name: Dialogue State

26269.content: Replacement drugs cost $100 for each urgent patient and $50 for each non-urgent patient.
26269.name: Dialogue State

26274.content: Because the cost of the replacement drugs is high, it is more important to treat urgent patients than non-urgent patients.
26274.name: Dialogue State
